    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>with your<strong> white wine vinegar</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>mustard dressing</strong></p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato & basil sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
